
// This Hyperlambda code splits a string and then joins the resulting parts with a comma. The [set-value] slot sets the value of the [.value] node to the result of the [strings.join] operation. The [strings.split] slot splits the string into parts, and the [strings.join] slot concatenates these parts using a comma as a separator.
set-value:x:@.value
   strings.join:x:@strings.split/*
      .:,
